"Work that will not lose its place,  \nEven when systems break their pace\u2014  \nA process paused by fault or night  \nReturns and carries on the light.\n\nEach step remembered, safely stored,  \nNot left to chance or one machine\u2019s word;  \nSo if a worker falls away,  \nThe task resumes another day.\n\nRetries bloom where failures land,  \nTimers wait with patient hand,  \nAnd state, preserved through storm and strain,  \nLets interrupted flows remain.\n\nDurable execution sings  \nOf steady, practical, stubborn things:  \nNot glamour, but a deeper art\u2014  \nTo fail, recover, and restart."